      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import yfinance as yf\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, LSTM\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6LSnXLoweLF7"
      },
      "source": [
        " **Loading Historical Stock Data Using Yahoo Finance API**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "opi6WnnGEzV1",
        "outputId": "8193ea4c-275d-470d-e895-bb2119daa6fb"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stderr",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "\r[*********************100%***********************]  1 of 1 completed\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "def load_data(ticker, start_date, end_date):\n",
        "    data = yf.download(ticker, start=start_date, end=end_date)\n",
        "    return data['Close'].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example: Load data for Apple stock (AAPL)\n",
        "data = load_data('AAPL', '2020-01-01', '2023-01-01')\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HU8Wt2HVe8rl"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Data Scaling and Preparation for Time Series Forecasting with LSTM**\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gcsx5OXzE5Wm"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0, 1))\n",
        "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(data)\n",
        "def create_dataset(data, time_step=60):\n",
        "    X, y = [], []\n",
        "    for i in range(len(data) - time_step - 1):\n",
        "        X.append(data[i:(i + time_step), 0])\n",
        "        y.append(data[i + time_step, 0])\n",
        "    return np.array(X), np.array(y)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ksQQMwVLfINe"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Preparing Data and Defining the LSTM Model Architecture for Time Series Forecasting**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "WGaMkcyXE_B_",
        "outputId": "ec9e35ad-eade-4943-c46b-daa632e1be8d"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stderr",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/keras/src/layers/rnn/rnn.py:204: UserWarning: Do not pass an `input_shape`/`input_dim` argument to a layer. When using Sequential models, prefer using an `Input(shape)` object as the first layer in the model instead.\n",
            "  super().__init__(**kwargs)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "train_size = int(len(scaled_data) * 0.7)\n",
        "train_data = scaled_data[:train_size]\n",
        "test_data = scaled_data[train_size:]\n",
        "\n",
        "time_step = 60\n",
        "X_train, y_train = create_dataset(train_data, time_step)\n",
        "X_test, y_test = create_dataset(test_data, time_step)\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train = X_train.reshape(X_train.shape[0], X_train.shape[1], 1)\n",
        "X_test = X_test.reshape(X_test.shape[0], X_test.shape[1], 1)\n",
        "# Define LSTM model\n",
        "model = Sequential([\n",
        "    LSTM(50, return_sequences=True, input_shape=(X_train.shape[1], 1)),\n",
        "    LSTM(50, return_sequences=False),\n",
        "    Dense(25),\n",
        "    Dense(1)\n",
        "])"
      ]
    },

            "Epoch 9/10\n",

            "Epoch 10/10\n",
            "\u001b[1m8/8\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m1s\u001b[0m 56ms/step - loss: 0.0019\n",
            "\u001b[1m15/15\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m1s\u001b[0m 35ms/step\n",
            "\u001b[1m6/6\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m0s\u001b[0m 14ms/step\n"
          ]

      "source": [
        "# Compile and train the model\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')\n",
        "model.fit(X_train, y_train, batch_size=64, epochs=10)\n",
        "# Predictions on train and test data\n",
        "train_predict = model.predict(X_train)\n",
        "test_predict = model.predict(X_test)\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "predicted_test_prices_scaled = model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "predicted_test_prices = scaler.inverse_transform(predicted_test_prices_scaled)  # Reverse scaling to get actual prices\n",
        "# Reverse scaling to get actual prices\n",
        "train_predict = scaler.inverse_transform(train_predict)\n",
        "y_train_actual = scaler.inverse_transform(y_train.reshape(-1, 1))\n",
        "test_predict = scaler.inverse_transform(test_predict)\n",
        "y_test_actual = scaler.inverse_transform(y_test.reshape(-1, 1))\n",
        "# Plotting\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))\n",
        "plt.plot(y_test_actual, color='blue', label='Actual Price')\n",
        "plt.plot(test_predict, color='red', label='Predicted Price')\n",

        "plt.ylabel('Stock Price')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2Tl2J515FDm9"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Calculating and Reporting RMSE for Model Evaluation**\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "background_save": true,
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "cMRqmkpOFiz5",
        "outputId": "bc31aabd-57ac-4a73-e449-db36ea724ec4"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Train RMSE: 5.279073302294799\n",
            "Test RMSE: 7.940120329885285\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
        "import math\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate RMSE for train and test data\n",
        "train_rmse = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_train_actual, train_predict))\n",
        "test_rmse = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test_actual, test_predict))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Train RMSE: {train_rmse}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test RMSE: {test_rmse}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UaWlTnobF-a0"
      },
      "source": [

      ]

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {

      "source": [
        "# Prepare dataset to plot actual vs. predicted data\n",

        "train_plot[:, :] = np.nan\n",
        "train_plot[time_step:len(train_predict) + time_step, :] = train_predict\n",
        "\n",
        "test_plot = np.empty_like(scaled_data)\n",
        "test_plot[:, :] = np.nan\n",
        "test_plot[len(train_predict) + (time_step * 2) + 1:len(scaled_data) - 1, :] = test_predict\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the results\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))\n",
        "plt.plot(scaler.inverse_transform(scaled_data), label=\"Actual Price\", color='blue')\n",
        "plt.plot(train_plot, label=\"Train Prediction\", color='green')\n",
        "plt.plot(test_plot, label=\"Test Prediction\", color='red')\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Time\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Stock Price\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.title(\"Algorithmic Trading using Deep Learning\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "F4MxEux5gY2-"
      },
      "source": [
        "Generating Trading Signals Based on Predicted and Actual Prices"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "background_save": true
        },
        "id": "WvNKPuvqIa18"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def generate_signals(predicted_prices, actual_prices, threshold=0.01):\n",
        "    signals = []\n",
        "    for pred, actual in zip(predicted_prices, actual_prices):\n",
        "        diff = (pred - actual) / actual\n",
        "        if diff > threshold:\n",
        "            signals.append(\"Buy\")\n",
        "        elif diff < -threshold:\n",
        "            signals.append(\"Sell\")\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            signals.append(\"Hold\")\n",
        "    return signals\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cXv6pXI-gbDz"
      },
      "source": [
        "Evaluating Trade Outcomes with Stop-Loss and Take-Profit Conditions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "background_save": true
        },
        "id": "vG-B961vIeSp"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "stop_loss = 0.02  # 2% below entry price\n",
        "take_profit = 0.04  # 4% above entry price\n",
        "\n",
        "def evaluate_trade(entry_price, current_price):\n",
        "    if (current_price <= entry_price * (1 - stop_loss)):\n",
        "        return \"Stop-Loss Triggered\"\n",
        "    elif (current_price >= entry_price * (1 + take_profit)):\n",
        "        return \"Take-Profit Triggered\"\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return \"Hold Position\"\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wLQ9zjq7g1qM"
      },
      "source": [
        "Backtesting Trading Strategy with Signal-Based Capital Management"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "background_save": true
        },
        "id": "thrxvluGIjOZ"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def backtest_strategy(signals, prices, initial_capital=10000):\n",
        "    capital = initial_capital\n",
        "    holdings = 0  # Shares held\n",
        "\n",
        "    for signal, price in zip(signals, prices):\n",
        "        if signal == \"Buy\" and capital >= price:\n",
        "            holdings += capital // price\n",
        "            capital -= holdings * price\n",
        "        elif signal == \"Sell\" and holdings > 0:\n",
        "            capital += holdings * price\n",
        "            holdings = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Calculate the final portfolio value\n",
        "    final_portfolio_value = capital + (holdings * prices[-1])\n",
        "    return final_portfolio_value\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LtsuyKNAhBuL"
      },
      "source": [
        " Executing Signal-Based Backtest and Portfolio Evaluation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "background_save": true,
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "pFOsDUviIoWo",
        "outputId": "48d57bb4-7871-4867-9a8a-f5a630650f9d"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Final Portfolio Value: [-514.09997559]\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "signals = generate_signals(predicted_test_prices, y_test_actual)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 5: Backtest the Strategy\n",
        "final_portfolio_value = backtest_strategy(signals, y_test_actual)\n",
        "print(\"Final Portfolio Value:\", final_portfolio_value)"
      ]
    }
